    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Add the <strong>black rice</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 30 min or until it's tender (it will still have a slight bite to it when cooked)</p> <p>Once cooked, drain and set aside</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the<strong> cucumber</strong> into discs</p> <p>Slice each individual <strong>cucumber disc</strong>&nbsp;into<strong> matchsticks&nbsp;</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>red</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop \ufb01nely</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;the juice of the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil</strong></p> <p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and half the<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) &ndash; this is your <strong>chilli-lime dressing&nbsp;</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pick the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems&nbsp;</p> <p>Pick the <strong>coriander leaves</strong> from their stems</p> <p>Set the<strong> mint</strong> and<strong> coriander leaves</strong> aside for garnish</p> <p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> stems finely, and add them to the <strong>chilli-lime dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> rice</strong> is done, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over the<strong> highest heat</strong></p> <p>Once your pan is <strong>very hot</strong>, add the <strong>beef strips</strong> with the remaining <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 1 min exactly, making sure you don&rsquo;t overcook them</p> <p>Once done, transfer them to a plate</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season the <strong>beef strips</strong>&nbsp;with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and leave to rest for 1-2 min</p> <p>Wash the<strong> baby spinach</strong> and pat it dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/asian-beef-strips-and-zingy-black-rice-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>black rice</strong> over the <strong>washed</strong><strong>&nbsp;spinach</strong></p> <p>Top with the <strong>cucumber matchsticks</strong>, <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>mint leaves</strong> and the <strong>rested beef strips&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p> <p>Drizzle the <strong>chilli-lime dressing</strong> and any<strong> resting juices</strong> all over and enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
